143            * semester in that order.
144            */
145           String[] semesters = new String[4];
146           semesters[0] = "" + year;
147           switch (semester) {
148           /*
149            * If the given year is 2001-2008, (year % 100) will give a single
150            * number below 9. Therefore, the previous, current and next semester
151            * all need a leading 0 added.
152            */
153           case 0:
154               semesters[1] = "WS" + "99" + "00";
155               semesters[2] = "SS" + "00";
156               semesters[3] = "WS" + "00" + "01";
157               break;
158           case 1:
159           case 2:
160           case 3:
161           case 4:
162           case 5:
163           case 6:
164           case 7:
165           case 8:
166               semesters[1] = "WS0" + (semester - 1) + "0" + semester;
167               semesters[2] = "SS0" + semester;
168               semesters[3] = "WS0" + semester + "0" + (semester + 1);
169               break;
170           /*
171            * If the given year is 2009, the previous and current semester will
172            * both be a single number and therefore need a leading 0 added. The
173            * next semester will be 10 and thus needs no adjustments.
174            */
175           case 9:
176               semesters[1] = "WS0" + (semester - 1) + "0" + semester;
177               semesters[2] = "SS0" + semester;
178               semesters[3] = "WS0" + semester + (semester + 1);
179               break;
180           /*
181            * If the given year is 2010, the current and next semesters will be 10
182            * and 11 and therefore don't need a leading 0. The previous semester
183            * will be 9 though.
184            */
185           case 10:
186               semesters[1] = "WS0" + (semester - 1) + semester;
187               semesters[2] = "SS" + semester;
188               semesters[3] = "WS" + semester + (semester + 1);
189               break;
190           case 99:
191               semesters[1] = "WS" + (semester - 1) + semester;
192               semesters[2] = "SS" + semester;
193               semesters[3] = "WS" + semester + "00";
194               break;
195           /*
196            * In all other relevant cases (11 and higher), the semesters can be
197            * used the way (year % 100) returns them.
198            */
199           default:
200               semesters[1] = "WS" + (semester - 1) + semester;
201               semesters[2] = "SS" + semester;
202               semesters[3] = "WS" + semester + (semester + 1);
203               break;
204           }
205           return semesters;
206       }

208       /**
209        * Calculates the data relevant for the balance into a balance course model.
210        * Returns that balance course model.
211        *
212        * @param course
213        *            The course to be calculated.
214        * @return The balance course model.
215        */
216       public static BalanceCourse getBalanceCourse(ICourse course) {
217           BalanceCourse balanceCourse = new BalanceCourse();
218           balanceCourse.setTitle(course.getDescription());
219           balanceCourse.setPart(course.getPart());
220           balanceCourse.setLecturer(course.getLecturer());
221           balanceCourse.setTargetAudience(course.getTargetAudience());
222           double plannedAWS = 0;
223           double basicAWS = course.getNumberOfGroups()
224                   * course.getUnqualifiedWorkingHours();
225           balanceCourse.setBasicAWS(basicAWS);
226           List<Employment> employments = null;
227           List<IAssistant> assistants = null;
228           try {
229               employments = (new Employment()).getEmployments(new Course(course));
230               assistants = (new Assistant()).getAll();
231           } catch (Exception e) {
232               e.printStackTrace();
233           }
234           for (IEmployment employment : employments) {
235               /*
236                * Sum up the budget costs of the course by multiplying the hours of
237                * the fitting employments.
238                */
239               if ((balanceCourse.getBudgetCosts().isEmpty() || !balanceCourse
240                   .getBudgetCosts().contains(employment.getFunds()))) {
241                   Double budgetCost = 0.0;
242                   for (IAssistant assistant : assistants) {
243                       if (employment.getAssistantId().equals(assistant.getId())) {
244                           budgetCost = budgetCost
245                                   + calculateBudgetCost(employment);
246                       }
247                   }
248                   if (balanceCourse.budgetCostExists(employment.getFunds())) {
249                       balanceCourse.addBudgetCostValue(employment.getFunds(),
250                           budgetCost.doubleValue());
251                   } else {
252                       balanceCourse.addBudgetCost(employment.getFunds(),
253                           employment.getCostUnit(), budgetCost.doubleValue());
254                   }
255                   plannedAWS = plannedAWS + employment.getHourCount();
256               }
257           }
258           balanceCourse.setPlannedAWS(new BigDecimal(plannedAWS).setScale(2,
259               BigDecimal.ROUND_HALF_EVEN).doubleValue());
260           return balanceCourse;
261       }

263       /**
264        * Calculates the budget costs of this employment
265        */
266       public static double calculateBudgetCost(IEmployment employment) {
267           String qualification = employment.getQualification();
268           double calculationFactor = 1.0;
269           double calculationMethod = Integer.parseInt(Runtime.getInstance()
270               .getOption("calc-method"));
271           if (calculationMethod == 1) {
272               calculationFactor = Double.parseDouble(de.aidger.model.Runtime
273                   .getInstance().getOption("pessimistic-factor", "1.0"));
274           } else {
275               calculationFactor = Double.parseDouble(de.aidger.model.Runtime
276                   .getInstance().getOption("historic-factor", "1.0"));
277           }
278           List<IHourlyWage> hourlyWages;
279           try {
280               hourlyWages = new HourlyWage().getAll();
281               for (IHourlyWage hourlyWage : hourlyWages) {
282                   if (hourlyWage.getMonth().equals(employment.getMonth())
283                           && hourlyWage.getYear().equals(employment.getYear())
284                           && hourlyWage.getQualification().equals(qualification)) {
285                       return hourlyWage.getWage().doubleValue()
286                               * calculationFactor * employment.getHourCount();
287                   }
288               }
289           } catch (AdoHiveException e) {
290               UI.displayError(e.toString());
291           }
292           return 0;
293       }

339       /**
340        * Checks all the semesters for their years and returns the years as a
341        * vector afterwards.
342        *
343        * @return The vector of years as ints.
344        */
345       public ArrayList<Integer> getYears() {
346           ArrayList<String> semesters = getSemesters();
347           if (semesters.size() > 0) {
348               /*
349                * Only get the years, if there are any valid courses with a
350                * semester.
351                */
352               ArrayList<Integer> years = new ArrayList<Integer>();
353               /*
354                * Check for every semester out of the semester vector, if the year
355                * of that semester is already noted and add it if it's not.
356                */
357               for (Object semester : semesters) {
358                   char[] semesterChar = ((String) semester).toCharArray();
359                   int year = 0;
360                   if (Character.isDigit(semesterChar[0])) {
361                       // The semester is in the form YYYY.
362                       for (int i = 0; i < semesterChar.length; i++) {
363                           year = year
364                                   + Character.getNumericValue(semesterChar[i])
365                                   * (int) Math.pow(10, 3 - i);
366                       }
367                   } else {
368                       // The semester is in the form SSYY or WSYYYY.
369                       int i = 0;
370                       while (!Character.isDigit(semesterChar[i])) {
371                           i++;
372                       }
373                       int power = 0;
374                       switch (semesterChar.length - i) {
375                       case 2:
376                           // The semester is in the form SSYY
377                           year = 2000;
378                           power = 10;
379                           for (int j = i; j < semesterChar.length; j++) {
380                               year = year
381                                       + Character
382                                           .getNumericValue(semesterChar[j])
383                                       * power;
384                               if (power == 10) {
385                                   power = 1;
386                               } else {
387                                   power = 10;
388                               }
389                           }
390                           break;
391                       case 4:
392                           /*
393                            * The semester is in the form WSYYYY. Both semester
394                            * years must be checked
395                            */
396                           for (int l = 0; l < 3; l = l + 2) {
397                               year = 2000;
398                               power = 10;
399                               for (int j = i + l; j < semesterChar.length
400                                       - (2 - l); j++) {
401                                   year = year
402                                           + Character
403                                               .getNumericValue(semesterChar[j])
404                                           * power;
405                                   if (power == 10) {
406                                       power = 1;
407                                   } else {
408                                       power = 10;
409                                   }
410                               }
411                               if (!years.contains(year)) {
412                                   years.add(year);
413                               }
414                           }
415                           break;
416                       }
417                   }
418                   if (!years.contains(year)) {
419                       years.add(year);
420                   }
421               }
422               ArrayList<Integer> sortedYears = new ArrayList<Integer>();
423               sortedYears.add(years.get(0));
424               for (int i = 1; i < years.size(); i++) {
425                   boolean addedYear = false;
426                   for (int j = 0; j < sortedYears.size(); j++) {
427                       if ((Integer) years.get(i) <= (Integer) sortedYears.get(j)) {
428                           sortedYears.add(j, years.get(i));
429                           addedYear = true;
430                           break;
431                       }
432                   }
433                   if (!addedYear) {
434                       sortedYears.add(years.get(i));
435                   }
436               }
437               return sortedYears;
438           } else {
439               /*
440                * There are no valid courses. Return empty vector.
441                */
442               ArrayList<Integer> years = new ArrayList<Integer>();
443               return years;
444           }
445       }

149       /**
150        * Determines all of the activity employments of a given assistant.
151        *
152        * @param assistant
153        *            The assistant of which to get the employments.
154        * @return The employments of this assistant.
155        */
156       public ArrayList<ActivityEmployment> getEmployments(Assistant assistant) {
157           ArrayList<ActivityEmployment> activityEmployments = new ArrayList<ActivityEmployment>();
158           try {
159               List<Employment> employments = new Employment()
160                   .getEmployments(assistant);
161               /*
162                * Map all the employments to their courses and sort them in
163                * chronological order.
164                */
165               for (Employment employment : employments) {
166                   ICourse course = new Course().getById(employment.getCourseId());
167                   addCourseEmployment(course.getDescription() + "("
168                           + course.getSemester() + ")", employment);
169               }
170               /*
171                * Create at least one activity employment for each course.
172                */
173               for (CourseEmployment courseEmployment : courseEmployments) {
174                   /*
175                    * Activity employments will be listed as time-period, course
176                    * and hour count. Because employments can have breaks, we need
177                    * to check if this is the case. If it is, we need to create a
178                    * new activity employment for the next time-period. Therefore,
179                    * we will set the name, year and month of the first employment.
180                    */
181                   ActivityEmployment activityEmployment = new ActivityEmployment();
182                   activityEmployment.setCourse(courseEmployment.getName());
183                   int firstYear = courseEmployment.getEmployments().get(0)
184                       .getYear();
185                   int firstMonth = courseEmployment.getEmployments().get(0)
186                       .getMonth();
187                   /*
188                    * This is used to check if the employment is in the
189                    * time-period. It is equal to the amount of months from
190                    * 1.1.0000 until today.
191                    */
192                   int firstTotalMonth = firstYear * 12 + firstMonth;
193                   activityEmployment.addYear((short) firstYear);
194                   activityEmployment.addMonth((byte) firstMonth);
195                   /*
196                    * This is the difference between the first month and the
197                    * current one.
198                    */
199                   int difference = 1;
200                   int count = 0;
201                   double hourCount = 0;
202                   for (Employment employment : courseEmployment.getEmployments()) {
203                       if (employment.getYear() * 12 + employment.getMonth() <= firstTotalMonth
204                               + difference) {
205                           /*
206                            * The employment is in the same month as the previous
207                            * one or one month after it.
208                            */
209                           hourCount = hourCount + employment.getHourCount();
210                           if (employment.getYear() * 12 + employment.getMonth() == firstYear
211                                   * 12 + firstMonth + difference) {
212                               /*
213                                * If it was one month after the previous one, we
214                                * will check for the next month.
215                                */
216                               difference++;
217                           }
218                       } else {
219                           /*
220                            * There is a break of at least one month between the
221                            * previous employment and the current one. We will have
222                            * to save the current activity employment and create a
223                            * new one.
224                            */
225                           activityEmployment.addHours(hourCount);
226                           int currentYear = ((firstTotalMonth + difference - 1) / 12);
227                           int currentMonth = (firstMonth + difference - 1) % 12;
228                           activityEmployment.addYear((short) (currentYear));
229                           activityEmployment.addMonth((byte) (currentMonth));
230                           activityEmployments.add(activityEmployment);
231                           activityEmployment = new ActivityEmployment();
232                           /*
233                            * Create a new activity employment with a new name,
234                            * starting month and year and a new difference. The
235                            * hour count needs to be reset as well.
236                            */
237                           firstYear = employment.getYear();
238                           firstMonth = employment.getMonth();
239                           firstTotalMonth = firstYear * 12 + firstMonth;
240                           difference = 1;
241                           hourCount = employment.getHourCount();
242                           activityEmployment
243                               .setCourse(courseEmployment.getName());
244                           activityEmployment.addYear((short) firstYear);
245                           activityEmployment.addMonth((byte) firstMonth);
246                       }
247                       count++;
248                       if (count == courseEmployment.getEmployments().size()) {
249                           /*
250                            * If this was the last employment of this course, the
251                            * activity employment needs to be closed. Add all the
252                            * relevant data to it and then add it to the vector.
253                            */
254                           activityEmployment
255                               .setCourse(courseEmployment.getName());
256                           activityEmployment.addHours(hourCount);
257                           int size = courseEmployment.getEmployments().size();
258                           activityEmployment.addYear(courseEmployment
259                               .getEmployments().get(size - 1).getYear());
260                           activityEmployment.addMonth(courseEmployment
261                               .getEmployments().get(size - 1).getMonth());
262                           activityEmployments.add(activityEmployment);
263                       }
264                   }
265               }
266           } catch (AdoHiveException e) {
267               UI.displayError(e.toString());
268           }
269           return activityEmployments;
270       }

688       /**
689        * Creates the balance reports of the year by calling the functions to
690        * create all semesters of the year.
691        *
692        * @param year
693        *            The year to be added.
694        */
695       private void createYear(int year) {
696           // Lose the first two numbers of the year
697           int semester = year % 100;
698           /*
699            * Contains the year in YYYY form, the previous, current and next
700            * semester in that order.
701            */
702           String[] semesters = new String[4];
703           semesters[0] = Integer.toString(year);
704           switch (semester) {
705           /*
706            * If the given year is 2001-2008, (year % 100) will give a single
707            * number below 9. Therefore, the previous, current and next semester
708            * all need a leading 0 added.
709            */
710           case 0:
711               semesters[1] = "WS" + "99" + "00";
712               semesters[2] = "SS" + "00";
713               semesters[3] = "WS" + "00" + "01";
714               break;
715           case 1:
716           case 2:
717           case 3:
718           case 4:
719           case 5:
720           case 6:
721           case 7:
722           case 8:
723               semesters[1] = "WS0" + (semester - 1) + "0" + semester;
724               semesters[2] = "SS0" + semester;
725               semesters[3] = "WS0" + semester + "0" + (semester + 1);
726               break;
727           /*
728            * If the given year is 2009, the previous and current semester will
729            * both be a single number and therefore need a leading 0 added. The
730            * next semester will be 10 and thus needs no adjustments.
731            */
732           case 9:
733               semesters[1] = "WS0" + (semester - 1) + "0" + semester;
734               semesters[2] = "SS0" + semester;
735               semesters[3] = "WS0" + semester + (semester + 1);
736               break;
737           /*
738            * If the given year is 2010, the current and next semesters will be 10
739            * and 11 and therefore don't need a leading 0. The previous semester
740            * will be 9 though.
741            */
742           case 10:
743               semesters[1] = "WS0" + (semester - 1) + semester;
744               semesters[2] = "SS" + semester;
745               semesters[3] = "WS" + semester + (semester + 1);
746               break;
747           case 99:
748               semesters[1] = "WS" + (semester - 1) + semester;
749               semesters[2] = "SS" + semester;
750               semesters[3] = "WS" + semester + "00";
751               break;
752           /*
753            * In all other relevant cases (11 and higher), the semesters can be
754            * used the way (year % 100) returns them.
755            */
756           default:
757               semesters[1] = "WS" + (semester - 1) + semester;
758               semesters[2] = "SS" + semester;
759               semesters[3] = "WS" + semester + (semester + 1);
760               break;
761           }
762           // Check if the semester has a course and add it if it does.
763           for (String currentSemester : semesters) {
764               if (courseExists(currentSemester)) {
765                   createSemester(currentSemester);
766               }
767           }
768       }
769  
770       /**
771        * Checks if the given semester contains any courses.
772        *
773        * @param semester
774        *            The semester to check
775        * @return true if the semester contains one or more courses.
776        */
777       private boolean courseExists(String semester) {
778           List<ICourse> courses = null;
779           try {
780               courses = (new Course()).getAll();
781           } catch (Exception e) {
782               e.printStackTrace();
783           }
784           // Check for every course, if it belongs to the given semester.
785           for (ICourse course : courses) {
786               if (course.getSemester().equals(semester)) {
787                   return true;
788               }
789           }
790           return false;
791       }

67               for (Employment employment : employments) {
68                   if (!months.contains(employment.getMonth())) {
69                       months.add(employment.getMonth());
70                   }
71               }
72           } catch (AdoHiveException e) {
73               UI.displayError(e.toString());
74           }
75           int[] sortedMonths = new int[months.size()];
76           for (int i = 0; i < sortedMonths.length; i++) {
77               sortedMonths[i] = months.get(i);
78           }
79           Arrays.sort(sortedMonths);
80           /*
81            * Since the controlling reports always include all the months of a year
82            * before the given month, all the months following the first month must
83            * be included.
84            */
85           if (sortedMonths.length == 12 - sortedMonths[0] + 1) {
86               return sortedMonths;
87           } else {
88               int[] fullSortedMonths = new int[12 - sortedMonths[0] + 1];
89               for (int i = 0; i < fullSortedMonths.length; i++) {
90                   fullSortedMonths[i] = sortedMonths[0] + i;
91               }
92               return fullSortedMonths;
93           }
94       }
95

97        * Determines all the funds the employments of a given year and month
98        *
99        * @param year
100        *            The year of which to get the funds.

102        *            The month of which to get the funds.
103        * @return The funds.
104        */
105       public int[] getFunds(int year, int month) {
106           ArrayList<Integer> funds = new ArrayList<Integer>();
107           List<Employment> employments;
108           try {
109               /*
110                * Since the controlling reports always include all the months
111                * before the given one, the funds of the ones before it need to be
112                * included.
113                */
114               employments = new Employment().getEmployments((short) year,
115                   (byte) 1, (short) year, (byte) month);
116               for (Employment employment : employments) {
117                   if (!funds.contains(employment.getFunds())) {
118                       funds.add(employment.getFunds());
119                   }
120               }
121           } catch (AdoHiveException e) {
122               UI.displayError(e.toString());
123           }
124           int[] sortedFunds = new int[funds.size()];
125           for (int i = 0; i < sortedFunds.length; i++) {
126               sortedFunds[i] = funds.get(i);

69                       inputStream = new FileInputStream(inputFile);

71                       Logger
72                           .info("Loading the translation from the filesystem failed. Only english will be available");
73                   }

76               /* Finally load the resource */
77               if (inputStream != null) {
78                   try {
79                       bundle = new PropertyResourceBundle(inputStream);
80                       inputStream.close();
81                   } catch (IOException ex) {
82                   }
83               }

85               /* Instanciate the selected locale and set it as the default for the jvm */
86               Locale def = new Locale(language);
87               Locale.setDefault(def);
88           } else {

137                           .getDisplayLanguage()));
138                   }
139               }
140           } catch (IOException ex) {
141           }

145           if (files != null) {

147                   String filename = file.getName();
148                   int idx = filename.indexOf(".properties");
149                   if (idx > -1) {
150                       String lang = filename.substring(0, idx);
151                       list.add(new Pair<String, String>(lang, new Locale(lang)
152                           .getDisplayLanguage()));
153                   }
154               }
155           }
156  
157           return list;

32  
33       /**
34        * Initialize the PresenceValidator class.
35        */
36       public Validator() {
37           this.model = null;
38           this.members = new String[0];
39           this.trans = new String[0];

43       /**
44        * Initialize the PresenceValidator class.
45        *
46        * @param model

48        * @param members
49        *            The members of the model to validate

53       public Validator(AbstractModel model, String[] members, String[] trans) {

56           this.trans = trans;
57           this.message = _("Default error");

60       /**
61        * Validate the input.
62        *
63        * @return True if it validates
64        */
65       public boolean validate() {
66           boolean ret = true;
67           for (int i = 0; i < members.length; ++i) {
68               Object value = getValueOf(members[i]);
69               if (!validateVar(value)) {
70                   ret = false;
71                   if (model != null) {
72                       model.addError(members[i], trans[i], message);
73                   }
74               }
75           }
76           return ret;
77       }

79       /**
80        * Validate the variable.
81        *
82        * @param o
83        *            The variable to validate
84        * @return True if the input validates, false otherwise
85        */
86       abstract public boolean validateVar(Object o);

88       /**
89        * Set the error message.
90        *
91        * @param msg
92        *            The new error message
93        */
94       public void setMessage(String msg) {

102        */
103       public String getMessage() {

105       }
106  
107       /**
108        * Get the value of the given member variable.
109        *
110        * @param name
111        *            The name of the member variable
112        * @return The value of the member variable or null
113        */
114       protected Object getValueOf(String name) {
115           String functionname = "get" + name.substring(0, 1).toUpperCase()
116                   + name.substring(1);
117           try {
118               java.lang.reflect.Method m = model.getClass().getDeclaredMethod(
119                       functionname, new Class<?>[0]);
120               return m.invoke(model, new Object[0]);
121           } catch (Exception ex) {
122               try {
123                   return model.getClass().getField(name).get(model);
124               } catch (Exception e) {
125                   return null;
126               }
127           }
128       }

130   }

36        *
37        * @param o The variable to validate

44       /**
45        * Validate the variable.
46        *

48        *            The variable to validate
49        * @return True if the input validates, false otherwise
50        */
51       @Override
52       public boolean validateVar(Object o) {
53           if (o == null) {
54               return false;
55           } else if (o.getClass().getName().equals(String.class.getName()) &&
56                       ((String) o).isEmpty()) {

23   public class ProtocolCreator {

26        * Initializes a new ProtocolCreator and creates the first protocol.
27        */
28       public ProtocolCreator() {
29       }
30  
31       /**
32        * Returns all the activities to the which are in the given time frame.
33        *
34        * @param numberOfDays
35        *            The number of days, of which to display activities.
36        * @return The activities
37        */
38       public ArrayList<Object[]> createProtocol(int numberOfDays) {
39           Object[] addedActivity;
40           ArrayList<Object[]> addedActivities = new ArrayList<Object[]>();
41           List<Activity> activities = null;
42           Calendar calendar = Calendar.getInstance();
43           Date currentDate;
44           /*
45            * The end date of the time frame will be the end of the current day.
46            */
47           calendar.set(calendar.get(Calendar.YEAR), calendar.get(Calendar.MONTH),
48               calendar.get(Calendar.DATE), 0, 0, 0);
49           currentDate = new Date(calendar.getTimeInMillis() + 3600000 * 24);
50           Date checkDate;
51           calendar = Calendar.getInstance();
52           // Display all activities if numberOfDays == -1.
53           if (numberOfDays != -1) {
54               calendar.setTimeInMillis(calendar.getTimeInMillis() - 3600000 * 24
55                       * numberOfDays);
56               calendar.set(calendar.get(Calendar.YEAR), calendar
57                   .get(Calendar.MONTH), calendar.get(Calendar.DATE), 0, 0, 0);
58               // Remove the milliseconds that it took to calculate the time.
59               calendar.setTimeInMillis(calendar.getTimeInMillis()
60                       - calendar.getTimeInMillis() % 1000);
61               checkDate = new Date(calendar.getTimeInMillis());
62           } else {
63               /*
64                * If the number of days to display is -1, set the check date to
65                * 1.1.1970 at 00:00. Since the calculated time is one hour after
66                * that, we need to subtract one hour in milliseconds.
67                */
68               calendar.setTimeInMillis(-3600000);
69               checkDate = new Date(calendar.getTimeInMillis());
70           }
71           try {
72               /*
73                * Only get the activities, that lie between the start (checkDate)
74                * and end (currentDate) of the wanted time frame.
75                */
76               activities = new Activity().getActivities(new java.sql.Date(
77                   checkDate.getTime()), new java.sql.Date(currentDate.getTime()));
78           } catch (AdoHiveException e) {
79               UI.displayError(e.toString());
80           }
81           for (IActivity activity : activities) {
82               /*
83                * If the date of the activity is after, or equal to the
84                * currentDate, it lies within the wanted time frame.
85                */
86               try {
87                   addedActivity = new Object[8];
88                   String assistantName = "";
89                   if (activity.getAssistantId() != null) {
90                       assistantName = (new Assistant().getById(activity
91                           .getAssistantId())).getFirstName()
92                               + " "
93                               + (new Assistant().getById(activity
94                                   .getAssistantId())).getLastName();
95                   }
96                   addedActivity[0] = assistantName;
97                   String courseName = "";
98                   if (activity.getCourseId() != null) {
99                       courseName = (new Course().getById(activity.getCourseId()))
100                           .getDescription()
101                               + "("
102                               + new Course().getById(activity.getCourseId())
103                                   .getSemester() + ")";
104                   }
105                   addedActivity[1] = courseName;
106                   addedActivity[2] = activity.getType();
107                   addedActivity[3] = activity.getDate();
108                   addedActivity[4] = activity.getContent();
109                   addedActivity[5] = activity.getSender();
110                   addedActivity[6] = activity.getProcessor();
111                   addedActivity[7] = activity.getRemark();
112                   addedActivities.add(addedActivity);
113               } catch (AdoHiveException e) {
114                   UI.displayError(e.toString());
115               }
116           }
117           return addedActivities;
118       }
119

121        * Returns the specified activity as an array of objects.

126        */
127       public Object[] getObjectArray(Activity activity) {

132                   assistantName = (new Assistant().getById(activity

135                           + (new Assistant().getById(activity.getAssistantId()))
136                               .getLastName();
137               }

BalanceReportSemesterCreator.java
18   public class BalanceReportSemesterCreator {
19  
20       /**
21        * The calculation method to be used for this balance report.
22        */
23       private int calculationMethod = 0;
24  
25       /**
26        * The vector containing the balanceReportGroupCreators and the names of
27        * their groups.
28        */
29       private final ArrayList<ArrayList<Object>> balanceReportGroupCreators = new ArrayList<ArrayList<Object>>();
30  
31       /**
32        * The balance helper used to filter the courses in this creator.
33        */
34       private BalanceHelper balanceHelper = null;
35  
36       /**
37        * Initializes this BalanceReportSemesterCreator and adds the groups of the
38        * given semester.
39        *
40        * @param semester
41        *            The semester of which the groups shall be added.
42        * @throws AdoHiveException
43        */
44       public BalanceReportSemesterCreator(String semester, BalanceFilter filters,
45               int calculationMethod) throws AdoHiveException {
46           this.calculationMethod = calculationMethod;
47           balanceHelper = new BalanceHelper();
48           addGroups(semester, filters);
49       }
50  
51       /**
52        * Adds the groups to the semester viewer.
53        *
54        * @param semester
55        *            The semester of which to add the groups.
56        */
57       private void addGroups(String semester, BalanceFilter filters) {
58           List<Course> courses = null;
59           try {
60               courses = (new Course()).getCoursesBySemester(semester);
61           } catch (AdoHiveException e) {
62               UI.displayError(e.toString());
63           }
64           List<Course> filteredCourses = balanceHelper.filterCourses(courses,
65               filters);
66           for (ICourse course : filteredCourses) {
67               if (course.getSemester().equals(semester)) {
68                   if (balanceReportGroupCreators.isEmpty()) {
69                       /*
70                        * If there are no groups in the semester yet, add a new
71                        * one.
72                        */
73                       createGroup(course);
74                   } else {
75                       boolean foundGroup = false;
76                       for (int i = 0; i <= balanceReportGroupCreators.size() - 1; i++) {
77                           if ((balanceReportGroupCreators.get(i)).get(1).equals(
78                               course.getGroup())) {
79                               /*
80                                * If the course group already exists in this
81                                * semester, add another row to it with this course.
82                                */
83                               ((BalanceReportGroupCreator) (balanceReportGroupCreators
84                                   .get(i)).get(0)).addCourse(course);
85                               foundGroup = true;
86                               break;
87                           }
88                       }
89                       if (!foundGroup) {
90                           /*
91                            * If the course group wasn't in the semester yet, add a
92                            * new group.
93                            */
94                           createGroup(course);
95                       }
96                   }
97               }
98           }
99       }
100  
101       /**
102        * Creates a new group and adds it to the balanceReportGroupCreators vector.
103        * Also adds the first course of the group to the group.
104        *
105        * @param course
106        *            The first course, which the group contains.
107        */
108       private void createGroup(ICourse course) {
109           BalanceReportGroupCreator balanceReportGroupCreator = new BalanceReportGroupCreator(
110               course, calculationMethod);
111           balanceReportGroupCreators.add(new ArrayList<Object>());
112           int i = balanceReportGroupCreators.size() - 1;
113           /*
114            * Add the group creator of this course's group as the first entry of
115            * the vector.
116            */
117           (balanceReportGroupCreators.get(i)).add(balanceReportGroupCreator);
118           /*
119            * Add the name of the group as the second entry of the vector.
120            */
121           (balanceReportGroupCreators.get(i)).add(course.getGroup());
122       }
123  
124       /**
125        * Returns all of the group creators of this semester.
126        *
127        * @return The group creators.
128        */
129       public ArrayList<ArrayList<Object>> getGroupCreators() {
130           return balanceReportGroupCreators;
131       }

49       public ControllingCreator(int year, int month, int funds) {
50           this.year = year;
51           this.month = month;
52           this.funds = funds;
53       }
54  
55       /**
56        * Calculates all the assistants of this controlling report, that match the
57        * criteria, as well as their costs.
58        *
59        * @return The assistant objects of this controlling report.
60        */
61       public ArrayList<ControllingAssistant> getAssistants() {
62           ArrayList<ControllingAssistant> controllingAssistants = new ArrayList<ControllingAssistant>();
63           try {
64               List<IAssistant> assistants = new Assistant().getAll();
65               // Get all the employments that fit the time span.
66               List<Employment> employments = new Employment().getEmployments(
67                   (short) year, (byte) 1, (short) year, (byte) month);
68               for (IAssistant assistant : assistants) {
69                   /*
70                    * There's no need to add the assistant, if there are no fitting
71                    * employments for it.
72                    */
73                   ControllingAssistant controllingAssistant = null;
74                   for (Employment employment : employments) {
75                       if (assistant.getId().equals(employment.getAssistantId())
76                               && employment.getFunds().equals(funds)) {
77                           if (controllingAssistant == null) {
78                               controllingAssistant = new ControllingAssistant();
79                               controllingAssistant.setName(assistant
80                                   .getFirstName()
81                                       + " " + assistant.getLastName());
82                           }
83                           new BalanceHelper();
84                           // Costs are needed pre-tax for this.
85                           double costs = BalanceHelper
86                               .calculatePreTaxBudgetCost(employment);
87                           controllingAssistant.setCosts(controllingAssistant
88                               .getCosts()
89                                   + costs);
90                       }
91                   }
92                   if (controllingAssistant != null) {
93                       controllingAssistants.add(controllingAssistant);
94                   }
95               }
96           } catch (AdoHiveException e) {
97               UI.displayError(e.toString());
98           }
99           return controllingAssistants;
100       }
101   }

BudgetCreator.java
16   public class BudgetCreator {
17  
18       /**
19        * The course budgets of this creator.
20        */
21       private final ArrayList<CourseBudget> courseBudgets = new ArrayList<CourseBudget>();
22  
23       /**
24        * Initializes a new BudgetCreator.
25        */
26       public BudgetCreator() {
27       }
28  
29       /**
30        * Adds a course budget to the vector of course budgets.
31        *
32        * @param course
33        *            The course of which to add the budget.
34        */
35       public void addCourseBudget(Course course, BudgetFilter budgetFilter) {
36           double totalBudget = course.getUnqualifiedWorkingHours()
37                   * course.getNumberOfGroups();
38           double bookedBudget = BudgetChecker.getActualBudget(course);
39           double availableBudget = 0;
40           if (totalBudget - bookedBudget > 0) {
41               /*
42                * If there are more budgets booked for this course than there are
43                * in total, the available budget shall be 0.
44                */
45               availableBudget = totalBudget - bookedBudget;
46           }
47           boolean foundLecturer = false;
48           boolean foundSemester = false;
49           ArrayList<String> lecturers = new ArrayList<String>();
50           ArrayList<String> semesters = new ArrayList<String>();
51           if (budgetFilter != null) {
52               lecturers = budgetFilter.getLecturers();
53               for (String lecturer : lecturers) {
54                   /*
55                    * If the lecturer of this course is included in the filter
56                    * list, it passed this filter.
57                    */
58                   if (course.getLecturer().equals(lecturer)) {
59                       foundLecturer = true;
60                       break;
61                   }
62               }
63               semesters = budgetFilter.getSemesters();
64               for (String semester : semesters) {
65                   /*
66                    * If the semester of this course is included in the filter
67                    * list, it passed this filter.
68                    */
69                   if (course.getSemester().equals(semester)) {
70                       foundSemester = true;
71                       break;
72                   }
73               }
74           }
75           if (budgetFilter == null
76                   || (foundSemester || semesters.isEmpty())
77                   && (foundLecturer || lecturers.isEmpty())
78                   && (compareBudget(availableBudget, budgetFilter
79                       .getAvailableBudget(), budgetFilter
80                       .getAvailableComparison()))
81                   && (compareBudget(bookedBudget, budgetFilter.getBookedBudget(),
82                       budgetFilter.getBookedComparison()))
83                   && (compareBudget(totalBudget, budgetFilter.getTotalBudget(),
84                       budgetFilter.getTotalComparison()))) {
85               /*
86                * If this course passed all the filters, it can be added to the
87                * list of courses that passed as well.
88                */
89               CourseBudget courseBudget = new CourseBudget(course);
90               courseBudgets.add(courseBudget);
91           }
92       }
93  
94       /**
95        * Compares a given actual budget with a given wanted budget by the given
96        * comparison method.
97        *
98        * @param actual
99        *            The actual budget that shall be compared to the wanted budget.
100        * @param wanted
101        *            The wanted budget, to which the actual budget will be compared
102        *            to.
103        * @param comparison
104        *            How the budgets should be compared. enum Comparison
105        * @return Whether the budget comparison was successful or not.
106        */
107       private boolean compareBudget(double actual, double wanted,
108               Comparison comparison) {
109           switch (comparison) {
110           case LESS:
111               return actual < wanted;
112           case LESSEQUAL:
113               return actual <= wanted;
114           case EQUAL:
115               return actual == wanted;
116           case GREATEREQUAL:
117               return actual >= wanted;
118           case GREATER:
119               return actual > wanted;
120           default:
121               return true;
122           }
123       }
124  
125       /**
126        * Returns the course budget as an object array.
127        *
128        * @param courseBudget
129        *            The course budget to be converted.
130        * @return The object array of the course budget.
131        */
132       public Object[] getObjectArray(CourseBudget courseBudget) {
133           Object[] objectArray = { courseBudget.getName(),
134                   courseBudget.getSemester(), courseBudget.getLecturer(),
135                   courseBudget.getBookedBudget(),
136                   courseBudget.getAvailableBudget(),
137                   courseBudget.getTotalBudget() };
138           return objectArray;
139       }

146       public ArrayList<CourseBudget> getCourseBudgets() {
147           return courseBudgets;

40        * @param course

42        * @param value

44        * @return False if the course will be over booked.
45        */
46       public static boolean checkBudget(Course course, double value) {

48                   * course.getNumberOfGroups();
49           if (plannedBudget >= getActualBudget(course) + value) {
50               return true;
51           }
52           return false;
53       }

57        *
58        * @param course
59        *            The course of which to calculate the actual budget.
60        * @return The actual budget.
61        */
62       public static double getActualBudget(Course course) {
63           double actualBudget = 0;
64           try {
65               List<Employment> employments = new Employment()
66                   .getEmployments(course);
67               for (Employment employment : employments) {
68                   actualBudget = actualBudget + employment.getHourCount();
69               }
70           } catch (AdoHiveException e) {
71               // TODO Auto-generated catch block
72               e.printStackTrace();
73           }
74           return actualBudget;
75       }

72           /* Get the path to the users home or config directory */
73           String home = "";
74           String os = System.getProperty("os.name").toLowerCase();
75           if (os.indexOf("linux") > -1 || os.indexOf("mac") > -1) {
76               /*
77                * Try using the XDG_CONFIG_DIR variable first. Provides the
78                * standard directory according to the desktop guidelines or a user
79                * set equivalent
80                */
81               String confdir = System.getenv("XDG_CONFIG_HOME");
82               if (confdir == null || confdir.isEmpty()) {
83                   /*
84                    * Otherwise just use the homedir and the hidden config
85                    * directory
86                    */
87                   confdir = System.getProperty("user.home", ".");
88                   confdir += "/.config/";
89               }
90               home = confdir;
91           } else if (os.indexOf("windows") > -1) {
92               /*
93                * Try using the APPDATA variable first. Should return the
94                * ApplicationData folder but may fail on older Windows versions.
95                */
96               String confdir = System.getenv("APPDATA");
97               if (confdir == null || confdir.isEmpty()) {
98                   /* Otherwise just use the homedir */
99                   confdir = System.getProperty("user.home", ".");
100               }
101               home = confdir;
102           } else {
103               home = System.getProperty("user.home", ".");
104           }
105  
106           configPath = home + "/aidGer/";
107           File file = new File(configPath);
108  
109           if (!file.exists() || !file.isDirectory()) {
110               firstStart = true;
111               if (!file.mkdirs()) {
112                     UI.displayError(MessageFormat.format(
113                           "Could not create directory \"{0}\".\n" +
114                           "Please make sure that you have enough rights to create this directory.",
115                           new Object[] { file.getPath() }));
116                   System.exit(-1);
117               }
118           }
119  
120           configuration = new Configuration();
121  
122           translation = new Translation(configuration.get("language"));
123  
124           /* Check if an instance of aidGer is already running */
125           if (!Boolean.valueOf(getOption("debug")) && !checkLock()) {
126               UI.displayError(_("Only one instance of aidGer can be run at a time."));
127               System.exit(-1);
128           }

166        * @return True if validation succeeds
167        * @throws AdoHiveException
168        */
169       @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
170       public boolean save() throws AdoHiveException {
171           if (!doValidate()) {
172               return false;
173           } else if (!errors.isEmpty()) {
174               Logger
175                   .debug(_("The model was not saved because the error list is not empty."));
176               return false;
177           }
178  
179           /* Add or update model */
180           IAdoHiveManager mgr = getManager();
181           boolean wasNew = isNew;
182           if (isNew) {
183               Logger.info(MessageFormat.format(_("Adding model: {0}"),
184                   new Object[] { toString() }));
185  
186               mgr.add(this);
187               setNew(false);
188           } else if (updatePKs) {
189               Logger.info(MessageFormat.format(_("Updating PKs for model: {0}"),
190                   new Object[] { toString() }));
191  
192               mgr.remove(pkModel);
193               mgr.add(this);
194               pkModel = (AbstractModel<T>) clone();
195           } else {
196               Logger.info(MessageFormat.format(_("Updating model: {0}"),
197                   new Object[] { toString() }));
198  
199               mgr.update(this);
200           }
201  
202           /* Add event to the HistoryManager */
203           HistoryEvent evt = new HistoryEvent();
204           evt.id = getId();
205           evt.status = wasNew ? HistoryEvent.Status.Added : HistoryEvent.Status.Changed;
206           evt.type = getClass().getSimpleName();
207           evt.date = new java.sql.Date(Calendar.getInstance().getTime().getTime());
208           HistoryManager.getInstance().addEvent(evt);
209  
210           setChanged();
211           notifyObservers(true);
212  
213           return true;
214       }

222       @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
223       public boolean remove() throws AdoHiveException {
224           if (isNew) {
225               return false;
226           }

228           /* Check if there is a custom validation function */
229           try {
230               java.lang.reflect.Method m = getClass().getDeclaredMethod(
231                   "validateOnRemove");
232               if (!(Boolean) m.invoke(this, new Object[0])) {
233                   return false;
234               }
235           } catch (Exception ex) {
236           }
237  
238           Logger.info(MessageFormat.format(_("Removing model: {0}"),
239               new Object[] { toString() }));
240  
241           getManager().remove(this);
242           setChanged();
243           notifyObservers(false);
244  
245           /* Add event to the HistoryManager */
246           HistoryEvent evt = new HistoryEvent();
247           evt.id = getId();
248           evt.status = HistoryEvent.Status.Removed;
249           evt.type = getClass().getSimpleName();
250           evt.date = new java.sql.Date(Calendar.getInstance().getTime().getTime());
251           HistoryManager.getInstance().addEvent(evt);
252  
253           setNew(true);
254  
255           return true;
256       }

455       /**
456        * Returns a string containing all informations stored in the model.
457        *
458        * @return A string containing informations on the model
459        */
460       @Override
461       public String toString() {
462           String ret = getClass().getSimpleName() + " [" + "ID: " + getId()
463                   + ", ";
464           try {
465               for (java.lang.reflect.Method m : getClass().getDeclaredMethods()) {
466                   if (m.getName().startsWith("get")
467                           && m.getParameterTypes().length == 0) {
468                       ret += m.getName().substring(3) + ": ";
469                       ret += m.invoke(this, new Object[0]) + ", ";
470                   }
471               }
472               if (ret.endsWith(", ")) {
473                   ret = ret.substring(0, ret.length() - 2);
474               }
475           } catch (Exception ex) {
476               System.err.println(ex.getMessage());
477           }
478           return ret + "]";
479       }

481       /**
482        * Extract the name of the class and return the correct manager.
483        *
484        * @return The name of the model class
485        */
486       @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
487       protected IAdoHiveManager getManager() {
488           String classname = getClass().getSimpleName();
489           if (!managers.containsKey(classname) || managers.get(classname) == null) {
490               /* Try to get the correct manager from the AdoHiveController */
491               try {
492                   java.lang.reflect.Method m = AdoHiveController.class
493                       .getMethod("get" + classname + "Manager");
494                   managers.put(classname, (IAdoHiveManager) m.invoke(
495                       AdoHiveController.getInstance(), new Object[0]));
496               } catch (Exception ex) {
497                   Logger.error(MessageFormat.format(
498                       _("Could not get manager for class \"{0}\". Error: {1}"),
499                       new Object[] { classname, ex.getMessage() }));
500               }
501           }
502  
503           return managers.get(classname);
504       }

506       /**
507        * Validate the input using the validators and a custom validate function.
508        *
509        * @return True if everything validates
510        */
511       protected boolean doValidate() {
512           /* Try to validate before adding/updating */
513           boolean ret = true;
514           for (Validator v : validators) {
515               if (!v.validate()) {
516                   ret = false;
517               }
518           }
519  
520           /* Check if the model got a validate() function */
521           try {
522               java.lang.reflect.Method m = getClass().getDeclaredMethod(
523                   "validate");
524               if (!(Boolean) m.invoke(this, new Object[0])) {
525                   ret = false;
526               }
527           } catch (Exception ex) {
528           }
529  
530           return ret;
531       }
